Job_Description:
Company Description

CWP Energy is a Montreal-headquartered energy trading firm with a satellite office in Pittsburgh. We have been active in all North American (including Mexican) electricity markets since 2012 and are a division of McGill St Laurent, a diversified commodity trading company.
Backed by a diverse team of specialists, CWP Energy has developed an expertise in renewable energy and trading physical & financial power on merchant markets.
Our business is underpinned by robust risk management, market experience and analytical capability.

Job Description

We are looking for a Junior Java Developer who is passionate and motivated to work on and improve our data platform that is used 24/7 by our experts in Energy markets.
You will contribute to the delivery of web applications/tools that help the team in their daily operations. We are in need of a fast learner and someone that is detail oriented, with a solution-oriented mindset and can-do attitude to overcome challenges. If you are able to thrive in a fast-paced environment and master frequently changing technologies and techniques, you are the person we need!

Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or technical discipline;
Professional experience writing applications in Java using Spring Boot with CI/CD methodology;
Hands-on experience with SQL database design and proficient at writing SQL queries specifically with Postgres;
Experience with Big Data.
Considered A Plus :
Experience with Python;
Experience with frontend development using React;
Experience with Kubernetes;
Experience with Google Cloud Platform (BigQuery, Dataflow, Cloud Functions or Datastore);
Experience in Finance.
Additional Information

Furthermore, your new working conditions will be the envy of all your friends and family:
Reimbursement (up to 80%) of your public transit pass (Opus, Tram, etc.);
Beautiful open-plan offices located in Old Montreal;
A unique culture and much more!

Job Requirements:
15+ years of experience
Proficiency in managing and leading study teams, timelines, and resources;
Expertise in statistical methods and modeling, writing SAPs, and mentoring less experienced statisticians and programmers;
Experience with FDA regulations, questions, advisory boards; experience with ISS/ISEs, BLAs, and NDAs. Strong programming skills related to complex statistical procedures (i.e. multiple imputation, mixed modeling, etc.);
Excellent verbal and written skills;
Demonstrated ability to convey statistical techniques and analysis to non-statistical peers.

