Since 1992, Ciena has been driven by a relentless pursuit of network innovation. We believe in a network that grows smarter, more agile, and more responsive every day. This means that when you digitally interact in your world - picking up the phone, streaming video, texting a friend or loved one – your interactions are being enabled by Ciena technologies. Ciena makes your social / entertainment / business existence REAL.
Job Description

What will you do at Ciena?
You will join the of the NPI Modem group, where you will be developing, building, troubleshooting, supporting data pipelines and data acquisition systems used in Ciena’s modem production lines.
New data analytics tools and new test systems are required for the next generation of manufacturing, and to grow our manufacturing capabilities, which is deployed around the globe, at manufacturing partner’s sites.



Responsibilities / Activities
Create and maintain optimal data pipeline architectures;
Assemble large, complex data sets for our different cross-functional teams;
Identify, design, and implement internal process improvements: automating manual processes, optimizing data delivery,
Transform data for the different sets of analytics tools;
Work with other test engineering teams to deliver data and analytical results fast;
Maintain security over our data;
Create data tools for analytics and data scientist team members that assist manufacturing for rapid predictive analysis and pattern matching;


Collaboration with stakeholders
Daily collaboration with team members, R&D engineers, test and process engineers;
Co-supervision of co-op students and research students from universities;
Frequent interactions with various team managers, internet security specialists, contract manufacturers;


Preferred candidates will have knowledge of:
Apache Spark;
Cloud computing (AWS, Azure)
Scala, Python, C#, ML;
SQL over a variety of databases;
Databricks;
MLflow;
Knowledge of version control and continuous integration (Bamboo, Git);
